### Task Completion Checklist Rule

**IMPORTANT: After completing each ToDo item, immediately update the GitHub issue checkbox.**

Use the following procedure to check off a completed task:

1. Get the current issue body:
   ```bash
   gh issue view {{NUMBER}} --json body -q .body > /tmp/issue-{{NUMBER}}-body.md
   ```

2. Edit the file to change the completed item from `- [ ]` to `- [x]`:
   ```bash
   sed -i '' 's/- \[ \] <exact task text>/- [x] <exact task text>/' /tmp/issue-{{NUMBER}}-body.md
   ```

3. Update the issue:
   ```bash
   gh issue edit {{NUMBER}} --body "$(cat /tmp/issue-{{NUMBER}}-body.md)"
   ```

- Check off items **one at a time**, immediately after completing each task
- Never batch-update all checkboxes at the end — update as you go
- This ensures the GitHub issue always reflects real-time progress
